race.comment: Competitive. CHERRY ROSE (3) resumes and has won 3/4 fresh. Won her only start here at the distance and is right up to this if presented on song. HEARTONI (2) has been racing in better provincial and metro company. Huxtable rides for the sharp Kendrick stable and he should go close in this grade. DEVIL DEVIL (10) was expected to delive the hat trick at Twin Hills but has excuses. The form prior stacks up and it's hard to risk this stable. DOUBTING EYE (7) won here first-up at this level and then settled back at Mackay as a $2.0 favourite. Loves this track/trip and will be fitter. Needs a good ride from the awkward barrier.
